Sentencas: We investigated the effect of current loading on the degradation behavior of an anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: Degradation behavior of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell using LNF cathode as function of current load

Sentencas: The cell consisted of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3(LNF), alumina-doped scandia stabilized zirconia (SASZ), and a Ni-SASZ cermet as the cathode, electrolyte, and anode, respectively.
Titulo: Degradation behavior of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell using LNF cathode as function of current load

Sentencas: The test was carried out at 1073 K with constant loads of 0.3, 1.0, 1.5, and 2.3 A cm(-2).
Titulo: Degradation behavior of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell using LNF cathode as function of current load

Sentencas: The degradation rate, defined by the voltage loss during a fixed period (about 1000 h), was faster at higher current densities.
Titulo: Degradation behavior of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell using LNF cathode as function of current load

Sentencas: From an impedance analysis, the degradation depended mainly on increases in the cathodic resistance, while the anodic and ohmic resistances contributed very little.
Titulo: Degradation behavior of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell using LNF cathode as function of current load

Sentencas: The cathode microstructures were observed using scanning electron microscopy (SEM) and transmission electron microscopy (TEM).
Titulo: Degradation behavior of anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell using LNF cathode as function of current load
